<plot>In this Universal "Name-Band Musical" (production number 6302), 'Jerry Gray (I)' (qv) and his band provide the music for vocalist 'Beryl Davis' (qv) and for 'Nita Bieber' (qv) and her dancers. 'Frankie Yankovic' (qv) and his Yanks provide their own. The music heard includes "What is This Thing Called Love", "Two-Way Stretch", "How Am I to Know", "Acapulco Polka", "Girl at the Typewriter" and "By the Waves Minntonka." It is not, by any stretch of revisionism or imagination, a "concert-film."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?275834</url></doc>
